v17: OOD generalization scope of a learned dictionary (superposition)
======================================================================

dictionary learned on D0-sparse targets; tested held-out on:

  in-dist (D0, sparse)    : learned=0.980  control=0.690  margin=+0.289  (genuine)
  OOD-dict (D1, sparse)   : learned=0.703  control=0.698  margin=+0.004  (no lift over random)
  OOD-dense (GRF)         : learned=0.679  control=0.709  margin=-0.030  (no lift over random)

[interpretation]
  in-dist margin +0.29: the dictionary recovered D0's structure and codes held-out
    draws from the SAME model -> B1 held-out realizability holds (not memorization).
  OOD margins (D1 +0.00, dense -0.03) ~ 0: generalization is WITHIN the
    shaped target distribution -- B1 holds there, but transfer to a different model
    class is narrow. Honest bound: the codebook is agnostic ACROSS the family it was
    shaped on, not across arbitrary distributions (as expected: a dict of D0-atoms
    cannot sparsely code D1-atoms). This matches how SAEs are dataset-specific.

